32 SECTION 3.
33 Said title is further amended by revising Code Section 27-2-4.2, relating to courtesy
34 nonresident fishing licenses to certain paralyzed or disabled veterans, as follows:
35 "27-2-4.2.
36 (a) The department is authorized to issue a courtesy resident or nonresident fishing license,
37 without fee, to any person who is not a resident of this state who is a paralyzed or disabled
38 veteran and who is participating in an organized fishing tournament event in this state
39 which is sponsored and conducted by a nonprofit charitable association of paralyzed or
40 disabled veterans or the department, provided that such tournament event is approved by
