41 the department. Such courtesy nonresident fishing license shall be valid for use only
42 during the specified dates of such tournament event and for a maximum of seven days and
43 shall include all requirements and privileges of a nonresident fishing license, including the
44 nonresident trout license, for use only in association with such tournament approved event.
45 (b) The department is authorized to issue a courtesy resident or nonresident hunting
46 license, without fee, to any person who is paralyzed or disabled and who is participating
47 in an organized hunting event in this state which is sponsored and conducted by a nonprofit
48 charitable association or the department, provided that such event is approved by the
49 department; provided, however, that persons disabled because of a mental impairment shall
50 be issued a courtesy fishing license only, pursuant to subsection (a) of this Code section.
51 Such courtesy hunting license shall be valid for use only during the specified dates of such
52 hunting event and for a maximum of seven days and shall include all requirements and
53 privileges of a hunting license, including the big game and any other requisite state hunting
54 licenses, for use only in association with such approved event.
55 (c) All courtesy hunting and fishing licenses are subject to all wildlife laws, rules, and
56 regulations with the exception of the provisions requiring the payment of fees as described
57 in Code Section 27-2-23 for such licenses. Such courtesy licenses may be revoked in
58 accordance with this title. It shall be unlawful for any person who has a courtesy hunting
59 license or a courtesy fishing license to permit the use of such license by any other person.
60 It shall also be unlawful for any person who is issued a courtesy hunting license or a
61 courtesy fishing license to use the license except at the department approved event for
62 which such courtesy license was issued."
63 SECTION 4.
64 Said title is further amended by revising Code Section 27-2-4.4, relating to special turkey
65 hunting season for young and mobility impaired hunters, as follows:
