66 "27-2-4.4.
67 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'mobility impaired person' means any person
68 who has been verified by a doctor of medicine currently licensed to practice by the Georgia
69 Composite Medical Board, the State Board of Examiners in Osteopathy, or an equivalent
70 body of another state to have any one of the following permanent conditions:
71 (1) Dependence upon a wheelchair or similar device for ambulation;
72 (2) Hemiplegia;
73 (3) Monoplegia;
74 (4) Paraplegia; or
75 (5) Single-leg amputation above the knee.
76 (b) The board shall promulgate rules and regulations authorizing the hunting of turkeys
77 during an extended open season to:
78 (1) Youth under 16 years of age Any person who is 16 years of age or younger; or
79 (2) Any mobility impaired person.
80 (c) Notwithstanding any provisions of Code Section 27-3-15 to the contrary, such
81 extended season shall be for the weekend prior to the first weekend of the open turkey
82 season, as established by the board.
83 (d) Such special authorization shall be subject to all other provisions of this title."
