92 Said title is further amended in Code Section 27-4-190, relating to commercial fishing license
93 with shellfish endorsement and master harvester permit or harvester permit, hours for taking
94 shellfish, and recreational harvesting, by revising paragraph (1) of subsection (a) as follows:
95 "(a)(1) It shall be unlawful to take or possess shellfish in commercial quantities or for
96 commercial purposes without first having obtained a commercial fishing license with a
97 shellfish endorsement and a master harvester permit or harvester permit or without proof
98 of purchase that such shellfish were purchased from a certified shellfish dealer. Master
99 harvester permits shall specify whether the permittee is authorized to take oysters, clams,
100 or other shellfish and shall only be issued to persons certified by the Department of
101 Agriculture to handle shellfish unless permission to take and possess shellfish has been
102 granted by the department as described in subsection (d) of Code Section 27-4-197 and
103 in Code Section 27-4-202. Such permits shall be provided annually. A permittee may
104 request authorization from the department for employees or agents, who shall be referred
105 to as harvesters, of such permittee to take shellfish from permitted areas. Such request
106 shall be in writing to the department and shall include the name, address, and personal
107 commercial fishing license number of the harvester. It shall be unlawful for harvesters
108 to take or possess shellfish as authorized under their employer's master harvester permit
109 unless they carry on their person while taking or in possession of shellfish a harvester
110 permit as provided by the department indicating the exact area and circumstances allowed
111 for taking. Such harvesters' permits and charts shall be provided annually by the
112 department and shall be in a form as prescribed by the department. Harvesters must
113 possess a valid personal commercial fishing license as provided for in Code
114 Section 27-4-110, a shellfish endorsement as provided for in the department's rules and
115 regulations, and, when a boat is used, a valid commercial fishing boat license as provided
116 in Code Section 27-2-8, unless the harvester is operating under a master harvester who
117 has purchased a valid shellfish crew license as provided for in Code Section 27-2-23 for
